This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama, issued on October 15, 2012, regarding the death of Arlen Specter. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on the day of Specter's interment. It also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff for the same period at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.